  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Boil a full kettle</p><p>Add your <strong>egg[s]</strong> to a pot of <strong>boiled water</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, cook for exactly 8 min for perfect, mid-boiled eggs, then fill a bowl of <strong>very cold water</strong> and transfer the <strong>cooked eggs </strong>to the bowl</p><p>Reserve the pot for later</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1635258327509-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1635258327509-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1635258327509-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1635258327509-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1635258327509-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add your <strong>bacon lardons</strong> and cook for 5-6 min or until golden and crispy</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1635258330120-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1635258330120-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1635258330120-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1635258330120-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1635258330120-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the eggs are cooked, add your <strong>basmati rice</strong> and 250ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[320ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[500ml]</span> <strong>cold water</strong> to the reserved pot and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to very low and cook, covered, for 10-12 min or until all the water has absorbed and the rice is cooked</p><p>Once done, set aside until later</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1635258335185-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1635258335185-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1635258335185-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1635258335185-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1635258335185-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Peel and finely slice your <strong>brown onion[s]</strong></p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Slice your <strong>chestnut mushrooms </strong>finely</p><p>Chop your <strong>tomato[es]</strong> roughly</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1635258339469-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1635258339469-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1635258339469-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1635258339469-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1635258339469-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the bacon lardons are golden, add the <strong>sliced onion </strong>and cook for 4 min or until softened</p><p>Once softened, add the <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>tomato</strong>, <strong>chopped garlic</strong>,<strong> sliced mushrooms </strong>and a knob of <strong>butter </strong>to the pan</p><p>Cook for 5-8 min or until the veg is tender</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1635258342737-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1635258342737-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1635258342737-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1635258342737-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1635258342737-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Peel the <strong>cooled eggs</strong> and cut them into quarters</p><p>Combine your <strong>ketchup</strong> and <strong>sriracha</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!) in small bowl – this is your <strong>spicy ketchup</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1646410406827-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1646410406827-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1646410406827-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1646410406827-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1646410406827-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the veg is tender, add your <strong>tomato paste</strong>, <strong>smoked paprika</strong>, <strong>curry powder</strong>,<strong> garam masala </strong>and a knob of<strong> butter </strong>and cook for 3 min or until fragrant</p><p>Once fragrant, add the<strong> basmati rice</strong>,<strong> blanched peas </strong>and a generous pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and<strong> pepper</strong> to the pan and give everything a good mix up</p><p>Cook for a final 2 min or until everything is warmed through</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1635258349289-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1635258349289-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1635258349289-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1635258349289-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1635258349289-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Top the rice with the<strong> egg quarters </strong>– this is your <strong>English breakfast kedgeree with bacon & egg</strong></p><p>Drizzle over the<strong> spicy ketchup</strong></p><p>Season with a pinch of <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8,
